Chima Azubuike, Gombe The Gombe State House of Assembly has passed into law the stateâ€™s 2020 Appropriation Bill of N130.83bn, reflecting an increase of N160m over N130.67bn presented earlier by the State Governor, Alhaji Muhammadu Yahaya to the House. This followed the adoption of recommendations contained in report of the House Committee on Appropriation presented on the floor of the House. Presenting the report, the Chairman of the Committee, Aliyu Manu, said the budget was made up of a capital expenditure of N71.05bn and a recurrent expenditure of N59.78bn. CopyrightPUNCH.
